# COMPILER/BOOT/iii_vmexit.def
#
# SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the KATABASIS minimal deterministic VMEXIT set
# (DOCS/III-KATABASIS.md plan 4.8).  The III Floor (R-1) intercepts the SMALLEST
# set of guest exits, each handled by a TOTAL deterministic witnessed cycle;
# every other (unmodelled) exit is FAIL-CLOSED.  This table fixes, per exit, its
# handling discipline and its SID inverse kind.
#
# Regenerate the AUTO-GENERATED taxonomy functions in
# STDLIB/iii/katabasis/vmexit.iii via:
#     bash COMPILER/BOOT/gen_vmexit.sh
# The build's drift gate (gen_vmexit.sh --check) fails if vmexit.iii's generated
# block diverges (plan 6.9 / FR-9).
#
# Each row maps to the hand-written enum constants in vmexit.iii:
#   exit const     = KVX_<kind>          (e.g. KVX_CPUID)
#   handling const = KVX_H_<handling>    (e.g. KVX_H_SYNTHETIC)
#   inverse const  = KVX_INV_<inverse>   (e.g. KVX_INV_IDENTITY)
# gen_vmexit.sh asserts every referenced constant exists.  The fail-closed
# CATCH-ALL tails (intercepted->0, handling->KVX_H_FAIL_CLOSED,
# inverse->KVX_INV_HOST_STATE) are the module's safety contract and are emitted
# by the generator for ANY unmodelled exit -- never table rows.
#
# Fields (whitespace-delimited):  kind  handling  inverse
#   kind      str -- exit name; forms KVX_<kind>.
#   handling  str -- handling discipline; forms KVX_H_<handling>.
#   inverse   str -- SID inverse kind; forms KVX_INV_<inverse>.
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Blank lines ignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# kind     handling        inverse
CPUID      SYNTHETIC       IDENTITY
MSR        WHITELIST       RECORDED
NPF        COW             COW
VMMCALL    WITNESSED_CALL  GUEST_REGS
SMI        OBSERVE         IDENTITY
INVALID    FAIL_CLOSED     HOST_STATE
